    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>This recipe takes around 5-10 min to prep, so get your casserole dish and all your ingredients ready, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Make sure your dish is oven-proof and safe to use on the hob. Don't have one? Start cooking in a large, wide-based pan then transfer to an oven-proof dish</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-chinese-style-braised-beef-and-broccoli-with-cauliflower-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based, <strong>hob-safe</strong> <strong>oven-proof casserole dish</strong> with a matching lid, with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>diced beef</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until lightly browned</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-chinese-style-braised-beef-and-broccoli-with-cauliflower-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and roughly chop your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely slice (don't chop!) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>Tenderstem broccoli </strong>roughly</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-chinese-style-braised-beef-and-broccoli-with-cauliflower-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Reduce the heat to medium and add the <strong>chopped onion</strong>, <strong>sliced garlic</strong> and <strong>cornflour</strong> and give everything a good mix</p><p>Add 400ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[520ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[680ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>with your <strong>beef stock mix</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat and put the dish in the oven, covered, and cook for an initial 50 min or until the sauce has thickened and the beef is cooked through \u2013 this is your <strong>Chinese-style braised beef</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-chinese-style-braised-beef-and-broccoli-with-cauliflower-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Use this time to clear up, set the table, have a cup of tea or simply chill!</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-chinese-style-braised-beef-and-broccoli-with-cauliflower-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the Chinese-style braised beef has had 30-35 min, reboil a kettle</p><p>Add your <strong>white long grain rice</strong> and <strong>cauliflower rice</strong> to an oven-proof dish with 120ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[250ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> and stir it all together</p><p>Cover tightly with<strong> tin foil </strong>and put the dish in the oven for 30 min or until all the water is absorbed and the rice is cooked \u2013 this is your <strong>baked cauliflower rice</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-chinese-style-braised-beef-and-broccoli-with-cauliflower-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the Chinese-style braised beef is ready, remove the dish from the oven</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped Tenderstem broccoli</strong> to the dish with your <strong>gluten free soy sauce</strong>, <strong>ginger paste</strong> and <strong>hoisin sauce</strong></p><p>Stir it all together and return the dish to the oven, uncovered, for 12-15 min or until the broccoli is tender and the sauce has thickened \u2013 this is your <strong>oven baked Chinese-style braised beef & broccoli</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-chinese-style-braised-beef-and-broccoli-with-cauliflower-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Leave the<strong> oven baked</strong> <strong>Chinese-style braised beef & broccoli </strong>to stand for 5 min before serving (this helps the flavours to develop!) then serve with the <strong>baked</strong> <strong>cauliflower rice</strong> to the side</p><p>Dig in!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
